  "rationale": "<p>Setting the two expressions for y equal: |x + 2| = x + 4. When x + 2 ≥ 0 this gives x + 2 = x + 4, impossible. When x + 2 &lt; 0 it gives −(x + 2) = x + 4, so −2x = 6, x = −3. Then y = −3 + 4 = 1. The solution is (−3, 1).</p>",
